content.description:
Found on the right side of the TW wall.

Start with your hands matched on the left facing sloper and your feet on the solid knee high ledge. Reach high for two crimp bars and mantle to finish.

There is one big chunk on the top which you can use to top out.

Surfed for 2 hours and feeling like your forearms and fingers didn't get enough of a workout? Well I got a route for you! Walk up to the TW wall at Mori point. The traverse starts on the left of the wall. Start with hands on the side pull jugs to the right of the small bush. Traverse left on various crimps and sloper pinches until you reach the nice jug above the B. Repeat 4 times back and forth and you will feel like the your fingers will be well worked.

If you want to add a top out, Â dyno from the nice jug to the sloper ledge to the right and top out.

Beware of breaking chossy feet.

1.5 star rock quality, 5 star views.

Highly Recommend at Sunset.
content.protection: Probably a crash pad to protect from an ankle roll and/or a friend to spot you from a fall back on the rocks. Bring the shoes your fine with wrecking so your not afraid of stepping off and catch yourself.
content.location: On the way left of the TW wall.
